19:T931,{"@context":"https://schema.org","@type":"FAQPage","mainEntity":[{"@type":"Question","name":"What is the difference between an AI strategy and an AI implementation plan?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"An AI strategy defines the direction — what you want AI to achieve for your business and why. An AI implementation plan is the operational document — the step-by-step roadmap for how you get there, including what to build, in what order, with what resources, and how you will measure success. You need both, and they need to be connected."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How long does it take to build an AI implementation plan?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"For an SME using the AI Navigator framework, the planning process takes 30 days. This includes four structured working sessions covering all 11 steps, with written outputs produced at each stage."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Do I need to be technical to build an AI implementation plan?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"No. The AI Navigator framework is designed for business owners and managers, not developers or data scientists. The process starts with business goals and workflows — things you understand better than any technologist."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"What does a completed AI implementation plan cost?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"The guided AI Navigator engagement starts at $997 for teams under 10 people and $2,497 for larger teams. Both include the full framework, all written deliverables, tool recommendations, and a copy of The AI Roadmap."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"Can I build an AI implementation plan on my own without a consultant?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Yes. The AI Roadmap — the book behind the AI Navigator framework — is a complete self-guided workbook that walks you through all 11 steps with templates, examples, and exercises."}},{"@type":"Question","name":"How is the AI Navigator different from other AI consulting approaches?","acceptedAnswer":{"@type":"Answer","text":"Most AI consulting starts with technology. The AI Navigator starts with business goals and ends with a written plan you own. The distinction matters because it changes who has the knowledge at the end of the engagement — your team holds a documented plan they can execute independently."}}]}f:[["$","$L2",null,{"id":"faq-schema","type":"application/ld+json","dangerouslySetInnerHTML":{"__html":"$19"}}],null,["$","div",null,{"className":"article-wrap","children":[["$","nav",null,{"className":"breadcrumb","aria-label":"Breadcrumb","children":[["$","a",null,{"href":"/","children":"Home"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":"true","children":" › "}],["$","a",null,{"href":"/resources/","children":"Resources"}],["$","span",null,{"aria-hidden":"true","children":" › "}],["$","span",null,{"children":"What Is an AI Implementation Plan? A Practical Guide for SMEs"}]]}],["$","h1",null,{"children":"What Is an AI Implementation Plan? A Practical Guide for SMEs"}],[["$","p","0",{"children":"An AI implementation plan is a structured, written document that tells a business exactly what AI to build, in what order, for what reason, and how to measure whether it worked."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"That definition matters because most businesses that attempt AI do not have one. They have intentions. They have a shortlist of tools. They have a manager who attended a vendor demo. What they do not have is a plan — a document that connects a specific business goal to a specific AI use case to a specific workflow to a specific build brief to a specific success metric."}],"$L1a"],"$L1b",["$L1c","$L1d","$L1e","$L1f"],"$L20","$L21","$undefined","$L22","$L23"]}]]
24:I[9456,["619","static/chunks/619-ba102abea3e3d0e4.js","549","static/chunks/app/(site)/resources/%5Bslug%5D/page-82b918b41d4220bf.js"],"default"]
25:I[6203,["619","static/chunks/619-ba102abea3e3d0e4.js","549","static/chunks/app/(site)/resources/%5Bslug%5D/page-82b918b41d4220bf.js"],"default"]
1a:["$","p","2",{"children":"The absence of this document is the single most common reason AI projects in SMEs fail to deliver measurable value."}]
1b:["$","div",null,{"className":"cta-box","style":{"margin":"32px 0"},"children":["$","$L24",null,{"href":"/","location":"resource_mid_ai-implementation-plan-sme"}]}]
1c:["$","section","0",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Why Most SMEs Do Not Have a Real AI Plan"}],"$undefined",[["$","p","0",{"children":"The pressure to adopt AI is real. Business owners in Qatar and across the GCC are seeing competitors move, reading about AI in every industry publication, and fielding calls from vendors promising transformation. The natural response is to start doing something — signing up for tools, running pilots, experimenting."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"A plan prevents this. It defines what you are trying to achieve before you select any technology. It documents your starting position so you can measure actual progress. It sequences the work so each phase builds on the last. And it produces written outputs at every stage — documents your team can refer to, your developers can build from, and your leadership can review."}]]]}]
1d:["$","section","1",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Component 1: The Strategic Vision Statement"}],"$undefined",[["$","p","0",{"children":"The first document in any AI implementation plan answers four questions with precision: What is the business goal? What is the AI use case? What are the expected outcomes? What are the success criteria?"}],["$","p","1",{"children":"This document — the Strategic Vision Canvas — is one page. It takes one working session to produce. And it is foundational to everything that follows. Every subsequent decision is tested against it: does this workflow, this tool, this feature serve the stated goal?"}]]]}]
1e:["$","section","2",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Components 2–11: From Starting Point to Execution"}],"$undefined",[["$","p","0",{"children":"A complete AI implementation plan built on the AI Navigator framework contains eleven components: Starting Point Assessment, Strategy Selection Decision, Strategy Preferences Profile, Prioritised Workflow List, AI Potential Ranked Task List, AI Task Canvas Documents, Optimised Process Maps, AI Tool Requirements Profile, Phased Implementation Plan, and Execution and Governance Framework."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"Each component informs the next. Nothing is skipped. By the end of the process, you hold a set of documents that are entirely yours — a complete AI Playbook for your business."}]]]}]
1f:["$","section","3",{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"What a Completed Plan Gives You"}],"$undefined",[["$","p","0",{"children":"At the end of a guided AI Navigator engagement, you hold a set of documents that are entirely yours. These documents are your AI playbook. You can hand them to any development team in the world and they can execute from them. You can present them to leadership and they can see the business case, the timeline, and the risk register without sitting through a technical briefing."}],["$","p","1",{"children":"Most importantly, they are not generic. They are built around your business, your workflows, your data, and your goals. No two plans produced through the AI Navigator framework are the same, because no two businesses are the same."}]]]}]
20:["$","section",null,{"children":[["$","h2",null,{"children":"Frequently Asked Questions"}],["$","$L25",null,{"faqs":[{"q":"What is the difference between an AI strategy and an AI implementation plan?","a":"An AI strategy defines the direction — what you want AI to achieve for your business and why. An AI implementation plan is the operational document — the step-by-step roadmap for how you get there, including what to build, in what order, with what resources, and how you will measure success. You need both, and they need to be connected."},{"q":"How long does it take to build an AI implementation plan?","a":"For an SME using the AI Navigator framework, the planning process takes 30 days. This includes four structured working sessions covering all 11 steps, with written outputs produced at each stage."},{"q":"Do I need to be technical to build an AI implementation plan?","a":"No. The AI Navigator framework is designed for business owners and managers, not developers or data scientists. The process starts with business goals and workflows — things you understand better than any technologist."},{"q":"What does a completed AI implementation plan cost?","a":"The guided AI Navigator engagement starts at $997 for teams under 10 people and $2,497 for larger teams. Both include the full framework, all written deliverables, tool recommendations, and a copy of The AI Roadmap."},{"q":"Can I build an AI implementation plan on my own without a consultant?","a":"Yes. The AI Roadmap — the book behind the AI Navigator framework — is a complete self-guided workbook that walks you through all 11 steps with templates, examples, and exercises."},{"q":"How is the AI Navigator different from other AI consulting approaches?","a":"Most AI consulting starts with technology. The AI Navigator starts with business goals and ends with a written plan you own. The distinction matters because it changes who has the knowledge at the end of the engagement — your team holds a documented plan they can execute independently."}]}]]}]
21:["$","div",null,{"className":"cta-box","children":[["$","h2",null,{"style":{"marginTop":0},"children":"Ready to assess your AI readiness?"}],["$","p",null,{"children":"The AI Readiness Assessment evaluates your business across five dimensions — workflow type, decision complexity, data availability, process volume, and team size — and gives you a personalised score with specific recommended next steps. It takes three minutes."}],["$","$L24",null,{"href":"/","location":"resource_bottom_ai-implementation-plan-sme"}]]}]
22:["$","div",null,{"className":"author-bio","children":[["$","p",null,{"children":[["$","strong",null,{"children":"Allan Sendagi"}]," is the author of ",["$","em",null,{"children":"The AI Roadmap"}]," and founder of SafeHaven AI. He works with SMEs across Qatar and the GCC to build structured AI implementation plans using the AI Navigator framework."]}],["$","p",null,{"style":{"marginTop":8},"children":[["$","a",null,{"href":"/","style":{"color":"var(--brand)","fontWeight":600},"children":"Take the free AI Readiness Assessment"}]," · ",["$","a",null,{"href":"https://calendly.com/allan-safehavenai/30min","style":{"color":"var(--brand)","fontWeight":600},"children":"Book a discovery call"}]]}]]}]
